    • setDnsTtlSuccessfulQueries

      public void setDnsTtlSuccessfulQueries(int ttl)
      Deprecated.
      Sets the TTL (in seconds) of successful DNS queries.

      Some values have special meaning:

      • Negative number, cache forever;
      • Zero, disables caching;
      • Positive number, the number of seconds the successful DNS queries will be cached.
      Parameters:
      ttl - the TTL in seconds
      Since:
      2.6.0
      See Also:
      • getDnsTtlSuccessfulQueries()

    • shouldResolveRemoteHostname

      public boolean shouldResolveRemoteHostname(String hostname)
      Deprecated.
      Tells whether or not the given hostname should be resolved.

      The names should not be resolved when ZAP is configured to use a SOCKSv5 proxy and rely on it for resolution.

      Note: Not part of the public API.

      Parameters:
      hostname - the name to check.
      Returns:
      true if the given hostname should be resolved, false otherwise.
